528
00:39:28,012 --> 00:39:29,365
Very well.

529
00:39:36,818 --> 00:39:38,214
Oh.

530
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:40,828
Here.
Here.

531
00:39:40,943 --> 00:39:42,696
Thank you.

532
00:39:43,107 --> 00:39:45,483
Dribbling down myself
like a child.

533
00:39:51,811 --> 00:39:54,310
Miss Claythorne's making
the coffee.

534
00:39:56,055 --> 00:39:57,884
She should be watched.

535
00:40:17,487 --> 00:40:18,630
Right.

536
00:40:19,748 --> 00:40:21,039
You do the stairs.

537
00:40:21,851 --> 00:40:24,494
I'm going to wash the guts
out of the wood store.

538
00:40:56,877 --> 00:40:58,006
Can I?

539
00:41:03,857 --> 00:41:06,533
I rather enjoy domestic tasks.

540
00:41:07,546 --> 00:41:09,299
They are soothing.

541
00:41:10,323 --> 00:41:11,600
Normal.

542
00:41:12,664 --> 00:41:13,616
Indeed.

543
00:41:31,171 --> 00:41:32,895
I'll just be a moment.

544
00:41:33,612 --> 00:41:34,779
All right.

545
00:43:28,628 --> 00:43:30,676
Stung by a bee.

546
00:43:33,269 --> 00:43:34,578
And then there were five.

547
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:59,092
Well, I suppose with no Rogers,
I should think about lunch.

548
00:43:59,209 --> 00:44:01,590
I could eat a scabby horse.

549
00:44:02,185 --> 00:44:03,656
You're actually hungry?

550
00:44:04,524 --> 00:44:08,301
Well, it was heavy work...
dealing with Rogers.

551
00:44:08,412 --> 00:44:09,959
And you're the one
who suggested lunch.

552
00:44:10,077 --> 00:44:13,096
Only because it's what one does
at this time of day.

553
00:44:13,211 --> 00:44:14,044
But I'm not hungry.

554
00:44:14,163 --> 00:44:15,277
How could you possibly
be hungry?

555
00:44:15,392 --> 00:44:17,264
Oi, you.

556
00:44:17,376 --> 00:44:21,153
Don't go implying...
casting aspersions...

557
00:44:21,263 --> 00:44:23,611
I've got... I've got nothing
to do with this.

558
00:44:23,722 --> 00:44:24,956
I've got nothing to do
with any of it.

559
00:44:25,071 --> 00:44:26,483
Just because I said
that I was hungry...

560
00:44:26,578 --> 00:44:28,958
I am hungry.
It doesn't prove a single thing.

561
00:44:31,338 --> 00:44:33,242
I'm going to get dressed.

562
00:44:39,311 --> 00:44:43,087
The whole morning, dragging
Rogers around, clearing up guts,

563
00:44:43,198 --> 00:44:45,006
without so much as a cup of tea
to wet me whistle.

564
00:44:45,102 --> 00:44:46,216
And you...
You look at me like...

565
00:44:46,331 --> 00:44:48,830
Calm down.

566
00:44:51,326 --> 00:44:52,635
You've got some front, love.

567
00:44:53,984 --> 00:44:56,569
You've got
some right brass neck.

568
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:02,036
Don't go downstairs on your own.

569
00:45:02,551 --> 00:45:04,098
Not with those two.

570
00:45:05,129 --> 00:45:06,439
What, Wargrave and Armstrong?

571
00:45:08,382 --> 00:45:10,405
You wait up here for me.

572
00:45:32,141 --> 00:45:36,187
It was locked, which means
there must be a master key.

573
00:45:36,306 --> 00:45:37,734
Rogers must have had
a master key.

574
00:45:37,852 --> 00:45:39,162
You two dealt with the body!

575
00:45:39,281 --> 00:45:40,666
And you found it.

576
00:45:41,184 --> 00:45:42,537
Or did you?

577
00:45:42,652 --> 00:45:44,286
You shrieking like a woman.

578
00:45:44,397 --> 00:45:46,063
Was that a bit
of amateur dramatics, was it?

579
00:45:46,182 --> 00:45:48,920
I did nothing to Rogers.
I didn't take any master key.

580
00:45:49,038 --> 00:45:51,104
We don't even know if there is
a master key.

581
00:45:51,219 --> 00:45:53,068
And we only have your word
that the gun was stolen!

582
00:45:53,163 --> 00:45:55,511
- You could've taken it!
- Why would I steal my own gun?

583
00:45:55,622 --> 00:45:58,002
I don't know
why you'd do anything, Lombard.

584
00:45:58,121 --> 00:45:59,950
I don't know
why you killed Rogers

585
00:46:00,065 --> 00:46:01,656
or Miss Brent or MacArthur!

586
00:46:01,770 --> 00:46:02,603
I didn't kill them.

587
00:46:02,722 --> 00:46:04,193
Well, you would say that,
wouldn't you?

588
00:46:04,309 --> 00:46:06,971
Just like you'd say
that your gun was stolen!

589
00:46:07,085 --> 00:46:11,489
You really are a first-class,
five-star,

590
00:46:11,607 --> 00:46:14,269
solid-gold fucking moron.

591
00:46:14,384 --> 00:46:15,975
Please, the lady

592
00:46:16,089 --> 00:46:18,318
Double bluff.

593
00:46:20,770 --> 00:46:21,960
What, Tubs?

594
00:46:22,078 --> 00:46:23,626
Why you would steal
your own gun.

595
00:46:23,744 --> 00:46:25,259
Armstrong's got a point.

596
00:46:25,371 --> 00:46:27,123
It's all riddles and games,
smoke and mirrors.

597
00:46:27,235 --> 00:46:28,750
Double bluff.

598
00:46:30,693 --> 00:46:32,565
You were the last one down.

599
00:46:34,342 --> 00:46:36,171
The last one.

600
00:46:36,921 --> 00:46:38,868
Ages behind everyone else.

601
00:46:38,983 --> 00:46:40,687
What... What took you so long?

602
00:46:43,148 --> 00:46:44,338
I don't care to say.

603
00:46:44,457 --> 00:46:46,568
You killed Rogers.

604
00:46:47,114 --> 00:46:49,300
You took the master key.
You went to bed.

605
00:46:49,415 --> 00:46:50,962
You made sure all of us
were downstairs.

606
00:46:51,081 --> 00:46:52,930
And then you got into my room
and you took my gun.

607
00:46:53,025 --> 00:46:54,182
You have my gun,
you little prick.

608
00:46:54,293 --> 00:46:55,408
Lombard.
For heaven's sake.

609
00:46:55,523 --> 00:46:56,680
I never killed Rogers,

610
00:46:56,793 --> 00:46:58,859
and I ain't got your key
or your sodding gun.

611
00:46:58,974 --> 00:47:00,132
Then what took you so long?

612
00:47:00,244 --> 00:47:02,354
If you weren't in my room
stealing my gun,

613
00:47:02,464 --> 00:47:03,698
then why were you the last down?

614
00:47:03,813 --> 00:47:06,712
I was in the bloody lavvy,
if you must know.

615
00:47:06,828 --> 00:47:08,375
Constipated!

616
00:47:11,984 --> 00:47:13,217
Oh, yes.

617
00:47:13,332 --> 00:47:15,218
Yeah.
Laugh it up.

618
00:47:15,634 --> 00:47:17,700
It's not funny.

619
00:47:17,815 --> 00:47:20,120
I was bound up something rotten.

620
00:47:20,671 --> 00:47:23,289
Sat there in a muck sweat.

621
00:47:23,407 --> 00:47:25,117
So it weren't me.

622
00:47:25,232 --> 00:47:26,779
It could have been any of us.

623
00:47:28,048 --> 00:47:31,110
Any one of us
could have had the key.

624
00:47:31,222 --> 00:47:33,883
Any one of us
could have the gun.

625
00:47:52,948 --> 00:47:54,715
It is the only way to be sure.

626
00:47:57,642 --> 00:47:59,634
It's not like you've been
singled out.

627
00:47:59,744 --> 00:48:01,554
We're all getting the same.

628
00:48:19,855 --> 00:48:20,925
No key.

629
00:48:21,044 --> 00:48:22,278
No gun.

630
00:48:24,495 --> 00:48:28,033
Now... Now you, Miss Claythorne.

631
00:48:28,144 --> 00:48:29,616
Of course.

632
00:48:48,333 --> 00:48:50,443
I'm just being thorough.

633
00:49:15,654 --> 00:49:18,034
You like Uncle Hugo, don't you?

634
00:49:18,153 --> 00:49:19,700
I do.

635
00:49:19,818 --> 00:49:22,004
I'm in love with him.

636
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:23,786
I love him so much it hurts.

637
00:49:23,904 --> 00:49:24,840
Silly.

638
00:49:24,936 --> 00:49:26,602
Girls are silly.

639
00:49:28,148 --> 00:49:30,096
And I'm going to marry him.

640
00:49:30,211 --> 00:49:32,949
I heard Mummy say he couldn't
afford to get married.

641
00:49:33,503 --> 00:49:35,288
Well, I'll find a way, Cyril.

642
00:49:35,407 --> 00:49:36,640
If you marry Uncle Hugo...

643
00:49:36,756 --> 00:49:38,389
When I marry Hugo.

644
00:49:38,501 --> 00:49:39,691
Will you be my aunt?

645
00:49:39,809 --> 00:49:40,642
I will.

646
00:49:40,761 --> 00:49:42,546
Aunt Vera.

647
00:49:42,665 --> 00:49:44,180
And what fun we'll have.

648
00:49:44,291 --> 00:49:47,548
Christmas and birthdays
and summer holidays.

649
00:49:47,663 --> 00:49:50,877
Picnics, parties, pony rides.

650
00:49:51,868 --> 00:49:54,454
How happy we'll be
when we have everything.

651
00:50:29,946 --> 00:50:32,250
Cyril!

652
00:50:58,035 --> 00:51:00,135
Why isn't Lombard doing this?

653
00:51:01,208 --> 00:51:05,131
Blore and I thought it a
good idea to keep you two apart.

654
00:52:08,310 --> 00:52:10,777
Well, well, Miss Claythorne.

655
00:52:13,030 --> 00:52:14,422
Mr. Lombard.

656
00:52:15,132 --> 00:52:16,323
Philip.

657
00:52:18,028 --> 00:52:19,143
Vera.

658
00:52:32,150 --> 00:52:33,259
Nothing.

659
00:52:33,775 --> 00:52:35,646
We'll search the rest
of the house.

660
00:52:35,757 --> 00:52:36,929
Every room.

661
00:54:47,239 --> 00:54:48,386
We're in hell.

662
00:54:49,261 --> 00:54:51,322
And we're being punished
for what we done.

663
00:54:51,838 --> 00:54:53,116
He refused the hood.

664
00:54:53,625 --> 00:54:54,782
He haunts me still.

665
00:54:54,895 --> 00:54:55,954
Look at them.

666
00:54:56,261 --> 00:54:58,027
There's something going on
between them.

667
00:54:59,195 --> 00:55:01,005
Someone has to come for us soon.

668
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:02,473
They... They have to.

669
00:55:02,588 --> 00:55:04,049
I reckon we're being watched.

670
00:55:08,081 --> 00:55:09,114
We are.

